14/03/2005
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Finnish diplomat Jaako Blomberg reportedly will be appointed European Commission (EC) special adviser on Cyprus, according to the weekend edition of the Greek Cypriot daily Fileleftheros. Blomberg is currently serving as Finland's special envoy for Cyprus and has worked on the Greek Cypriot state's admission to the EU. 
On Friday (11 March), Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan called on the EC to assist in the process of resolving the Cyprus issue. He stressed that while the UN is the official body in chrage of dealing with the issue, the EC could help. (Fileleftheros, NTV, TurkishPress.com - 12/03/05)
